&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Clinical/Counselling &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Psychologists&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;8a&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;3.0wte, UK wide, 18months fixed-term or NHS secondment&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We are pleased to advertise this unique and exciting opportunity for Clinical/Counselling Psychologists to join a small team of psychologists forming a bespoke Maternity Review Psychological Service (MRPS). This team will be led by a Consultant Psychologist and provide psychological input to support women and families who have come forward to the OckendenIndependentMaternity Review, which is investigating adverse maternity experiences in Shropshire and Telford and Wrekin Maternity Services.This Service is being commissioned by NHSE for an 18 month period (with review and possible extension of additional 3-6 months) and we are seeking to recruit nationally, on a fixed-term contract or through NHS secondment.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;These families’ experiences span a 40 yearperiod and so the families come in many configurations, including older adults, couples, intergenerationalgroupings, children, and also adolescents and adults with birth- related disabilities.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The clinical model is trauma-informed and based on a psychological strength-based, consultation and intervention approach which seeks to normalise, validate and assist families in furthering their psychological understanding and enhancing their ways of coping and thriving despite these difficult and often traumatic experiences.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;The team will work flexibly, though given the current pandemic this will be remotely where possible. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Several families have moved since their adverse maternity experience and so some clinical work will involve work across the UK. Hence our recruitment is on a national basis. This NHSE commissioned service is being hosted by MPFT, within the Shropshire, Telford and Wrekin Care Group and administrative, operational and professional support is built into the service specification. Although working largely remotely, you will be networked into Shropshire and Telford and Wrekin Mental Health Services, and you will be professionallysupported and have the availability of consultation space whereyour most senior professional support is based.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;In stepping into this role, you will have a community focus, be trauma-informed and systemically skilled, with confidence in working flexibly across clinical specialisms and the full lifespan. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;You will be supported by the Consultant Psychologist within the Service as well as other colleagues within the team and you will also be networked into the peer support of psychological colleagues within the Care Group and across the Trust, which has Services across the UK.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;If you are interested and excited about this opportunity and have the skills and qualities we seek, we warmly invite you to apply.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;We welcome NHS secondments for this opportunity and also offer as an 18 month fixed term contract. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;If you would like to discuss this furtherplease contact,&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Dr Rachel Lucas (Director of Psychological Services), rachel.lucas@mpft.nhs.uk and/or &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Dr Gillian Roose (Consultant Clinical Psychologist, Lead for Psychological Practice, Shropshire, Telford and Wrekin Care Group), gillian.roose@mpft.nhs.uk&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Closing date:&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;19.11.2020&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Interview date:&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;25.11.2020&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
